    "title": [
      "[Olbin Delta, Covered Bridge]"
    ],
    "description": [
      "Moss flourishes in the cracks of a covered stone bridge spanning a shallow distributary of the river that gives the valley its name.  Fish thrive in the clear waters below, gleaming with scales in colors reminiscent of coins: brazen golds, dusky silvers, and ruddy coppers.  Above the entrance to the bridge is a carved effigy that looks like a bramble branch silhouetted against a moon."
    ],
